  "prompt": "Can a judge force someone to stop taking their legally prescribed buprenorphine?",
  "response": "Generally, a judge cannot force someone to stop taking a legally prescribed medication like buprenorphine, which is used to treat opioid addiction. However, specific circumstances can vary depending on the legal context (such as drug court, probation, or custody cases). If there are concerns about medication use, a judge might:\n\n1. Request a medical review\n2. Ask for additional medical documentation\n3. Consult with medical professionals\n\nThe ultimate medical decision typically remains with the prescribing physician.",
